NUMBER 2305
NAME Northern Vale
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 134
REGION 103
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are standing in a small bordered by sheer cliffs. The ground is almost bare
except for a few stalks of mountain grass which struggle to find life in the
rocky soil. To the north is what may have once been a pass out of the vale, but
it is now blocked with huge boulders that appear to have fallen from the cliffs
above at one time in the past. A tall granite tower can be seen to the south.
*DESCRIPTION_END
